Package: linux-hello
Architecture: all
Depends:
  ${misc:Depends},
  linux-hello-daemon (= ${source:Version}),
  linux-hello-tools (= ${source:Version}),
  libpam-linux-hello (= ${source:Version})
Description: Face Authentication System for Linux (metapackage)
 Linux Hello provides facial recognition authentication for:
 .
 .
  * sudo authentication
  * screenlock unlock (KDE/GNOME)
  * login screen (future)
 .
 This is a metapackage: installing it pulls in the daemon, the ONNX
 models, the CLI, and the PAM integration — everything needed for a
 complete, enrollable setup. The graphical configuration app is a
 separate, optional package (linux-hello-gui).

Package: linux-hello-daemon
Architecture: any
Depends:
  ${shlibs:Depends},
  ${misc:Depends},
  dbus,
  systemd,
  libonnxruntime1.23,
  linux-hello-models
Description: Face Authentication System for Linux — daemon
 Linux Hello provides facial recognition authentication for:
 .
 .
  * sudo authentication
  * screenlock unlock (KDE/GNOME)
  * login screen (future)
 .
 This package includes the daemon and PAM module library.

Package: linux-hello-models
Architecture: all
Depends:
  ${misc:Depends}
Description: ONNX models for Linux Hello face authentication
 This package contains the ONNX neural network models required by Linux Hello
 for face detection and embedding extraction.
 .
 Models installed in /usr/share/linux-hello/models/:
 .
  * det_500m.onnx — SCRFD-500M face detector (~500 KB)
  * w600k_mbf.onnx — ArcFace MobileNetV3 face embedding (~2.5 MB)

Package: libpam-linux-hello
Architecture: any
Depends:
  ${shlibs:Depends},
  ${misc:Depends},
  linux-hello-daemon,
  linux-hello-tools,
  libpam-runtime
Description: PAM module for Linux Hello
 This PAM module integrates Linux Hello facial recognition
 with system authentication (sudo, screenlock, etc).
 .
 Installing this package pulls in everything needed for a working
 setup: the daemon, the ONNX models, and the linux-hello CLI for
 enrolling faces. The graphical configuration app is a separate,
 optional package (linux-hello-gui).

Package: linux-hello-tools
Architecture: any
Depends:
  ${shlibs:Depends},
  ${misc:Depends},
  linux-hello-daemon
Description: Command-line tools for Linux Hello
 Includes the linux-hello CLI for managing faces and testing.

Package: linux-hello-gui
Architecture: any
Depends:
  ${shlibs:Depends},
  ${misc:Depends},
  linux-hello-daemon,
  pkexec,
  qml-qt6,
  qml6-module-org-kde-kirigami,
  qml6-module-qtcore,
  qml6-module-qtquick,
  qml6-module-qtquick-layouts,
  qml6-module-qtquick-controls
Recommends: kde-plasma-desktop
Description: Configuration GUI for Linux Hello
 Graphical interface for managing Linux Hello facial authentication.
 Provides a Qt/Kirigami-based settings application with support
 for 10 languages (English, Chinese, Spanish, Hindi, Arabic,
 Portuguese, Russian, Japanese, German, French).
 .
 Features:
 .
 .
  * Face registration and management
  * Authentication settings configuration
  * Multi-language support with instant switching
  * System integration with KDE Plasma and GNOME
